commit.message: Added the release version
Updated changelog for PR #138

Added support for alternative parameter names

Fixes #144.
Fixed inconsistent data class formatting
Fixed flake8 error

Fixed formatting of parametrized IO annotation

Fixes #142.
Updated test results to match Sphinx 3.0+ output
Dropped support for Sphinx < 3.0
Enabled coveralls parallel build reporting
Added .pre-commit-config.yaml to .gitignore

Update import path for Signature (#138)

The sphinx.util.inspect.Signature api has been deprecated since sphinx
2.4 and is staged for removal in the 4.0 release. [1] This commit updates
the import path to use the alternative function for it that is not
deprecated. This should avoid raising a deprecation warning on each
function signature that is using typehints.

Fixes #133

[1] https://www.sphinx-doc.org/en/latest/extdev/deprecated.html?highlight=signature

The sphinx.util.inspect.Signature api has been deprecated since sphinx
2.4 and is staged for removal in the 4.0 release. [1] This commit updates
the import path to use the alternative function for it that is not
deprecated. This should avoid raising a deprecation warning on each
function signature that is using typehints.

Fixes #133

commit.message:
Fixed TypeError with generic classes having the "name" property

Fixes #118.

Fixed inner classes missing their parent name(s)

Fixes #117.

Fixed KeyError when encountering mocked annotations

Fixes #116.
Added the release version

Fixed decorator classes not being processed as classes

Fixes #111.

Rewrote the annotation formatting logic

This fixes multiple annoying issues and makes the code easier to read.
Fixes #113.

Fixed Sphinx inventory caching

When running across several Python versions, the cached py3.5 objects.inv would have been used for 3.7 too.

Fixed class name parsing for plain typing.* classes

Fixes #114.

Added test for typing.IO

This failed to work properly despite the rest of the test suite passing.

Added test job for Python 3.5.2

This is the minimum supported version.
Added the release version
Switched to the official Python 3.8 release in Travis config
Updated the changelog for PR #107

Introduce typehints_document_rtype config. (#107)

If typehints_document_rtype=False (default True), never add an :rtype: directive.

Closes #106.
Added the .vscode directory to .gitignore (#110)

Fixed rendering of unparametrized typing.* types

Fixes #86.
Added a bunch of useful default options to pytest config

Fixed OSError when generating docs for SQLAlchemy mapped classes

Fixes #104.

Added support for typing_extensions

Closes #109.
